        "lessons": [
          {
            "title": "Intro",
            "id": 78785,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Let's learn how to display different kinds of values together in the console with a handy feature known as formatted strings.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Adding strings",
            "id": 78795,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We've learned that we can use <code>+</code> to add two strings and display them together.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;new&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\" + \" /><text value=\"&quot; messages&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"12\" endIndex=\"13\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"=\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"new messages\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>+</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Adding numbers and strings",
            "id": 78796,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>But using <code>+</code> to combine numeric data like <code>2</code> and <code>\" new messages\"</code> together produces an <strong>error</strong> as they are different kinds of values.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\" + \" /><text value=\"&quot; new messages&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"8\" endIndex=\"9\" /><option startIndex=\"10\" endIndex=\"25\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Traceback (most recent call last):\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  File &quot;/home/default/code/file.py&quot;, line 1, in &lt;module&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"    print(2 + &quot; new messages&quot;)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for +: 'int' and 'str'\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>+</code>, followed by <code>\" new messages\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Formatted strings",
            "id": 78797,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>f-strings, short for formatted strings, allow us to display expressions like adding a string to a number, without any error.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\" new messages&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"6\" endIndex=\"25\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"2 new messages\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>f\"{2} new messages\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Formatted strings",
            "id": 78798,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Every f-string statement consists of two parts, first the character <code>f</code>, then the string that we want to format.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"6\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\" new messages&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"6\" endIndex=\"7\" /><option startIndex=\"7\" endIndex=\"25\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"6 new messages\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>f</code>, followed by <code>\"{6} new messages\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Formatted strings",
            "id": 78799,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Next, we add the different kind of value in curly braces so it'll display as one print statement. Like here, with <code>{2}</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\" new messages&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"8\" endIndex=\"11\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"2 new messages\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>{2}</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Formatted strings",
            "id": 78800,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Inserting variables like <code>new_messages</code> between the curly braces displays their value too.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"new_messages = \" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{new_messages}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\" new messages&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"26\" endIndex=\"38\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"2\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"2 new messages\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>new_messages</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Expressions",
            "id": 80749,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can also use expressions like <code>new - read</code> between the curly braces to display their value.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"new = \" /><text value=\"5\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"read = \" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{new - read}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\" unread messages&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"27\" endIndex=\"37\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"3 unread messages\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>new - read</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Formatted strings",
            "id": 78802,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can use curly braces to insert values as often as we like inside the f-string. See it here with <code>5</code>, and then with <code>2</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"5\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\" new messages and \" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\" friend requests&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"9\" endIndex=\"10\" /><option startIndex=\"30\" endIndex=\"31\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"5 new messages and 2 friend requests\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>5</code>, followed by <code>2</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Formatted strings",
            "id": 82107,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To reuse an f-string, we can save it in a variable, like here with <code>status</code> and <code>f\"{new} new messages\"</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"new = \" /><text value=\"5\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"status = \" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{new}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\" new messages&quot;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(status)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"8\" endIndex=\"14\" /><option startIndex=\"15\" endIndex=\"16\" /><option startIndex=\"17\" endIndex=\"38\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"5 new messages\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>status</code>, followed by <code>=</code>, and finally <code>f\"{new} new messages\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: f-strings",
            "id": 78991,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What are f-strings for?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">For displaying different kinds of values together in a string</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">For displaying just string values together</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">For displaying different kinds of values together in a string.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: The character f",
            "id": 78992,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>How do we recognize an f-string?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">By the character <code>f</code> in front of the string</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">There's no difference between strings and f-strings</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">By the character <code>f</code> in front of the string.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: Curly braces for values",
            "id": 78993,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>How do we display number values with f-strings?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">We place them between curly braces, <code>{}</code></item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">We can't display number values with f-strings</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">We place them between curly braces, <code>{}</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: Save in a variable",
            "id": 82108,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>How can we reuse an f-string we created?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">We save it in a variable and use the variable</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">We can't reuse f-strings</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">We save it in a variable and use the variable.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Example: f-strings",
            "id": 78997,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Display the f-string.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;\" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\" dataset entries&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"6\" endIndex=\"28\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"&quot;4 dataset entries&quot;\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"4 dataset entries\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>f\"{4} dataset entries\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Example: The character f",
            "id": 78998,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Code the character <code>f</code> before the formatted string.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;popularity increased by \" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"12\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\"%&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"6\" endIndex=\"7\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"popularity increased by 12%\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>f</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Example: Curly braces for values",
            "id": 78999,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Display <code>500</code> inside the string by coding <code>{500}</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;I would walk \" /><text value=\"{\" /><text value=\"500\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text value=\" miles&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"21\" endIndex=\"26\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"I would walk 500 miles\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>{500}</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Example: Variables",
            "id": 79001,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Display the current temperature by coding <code>degrees</code> between curly braces.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"degrees = \" /><text value=\"70\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;Temperature: \" /><text value=\"{degrees}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\"F&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"34\" endIndex=\"35\" /><option startIndex=\"35\" endIndex=\"42\" /><option startIndex=\"42\" endIndex=\"43\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"print\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Temperature: 70F\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>{</code>, followed by <code>degrees</code>, and finally <code>}</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Example: Save in a variable",
            "id": 82109,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Save the f-string in the variable <code>display</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"movie = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Vertigo&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"display = \" /><text value=\"f&quot;Airing tonight: \" /><text value=\"{movie}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\"&quot;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(display)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"18\" endIndex=\"25\" /><option startIndex=\"26\" endIndex=\"27\" /><option startIndex=\"28\" endIndex=\"29\" /><option startIndex=\"29\" endIndex=\"54\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Airing tonight: Vertigo\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>display</code> followed by <code>=</code> and then <code>f</code>, <code>\"Airing tonight: {movie}\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
